<span id="freeTextContainer319542702232689075">This is probably the slowest book I’ve ever read. And I’ve read Musil, Joyce and Wallace. Some sentences run 5 pages. It is a very hard work. And yet it is worth reading. It is poetic, it is about overcoming limits and seeing beyond them. <br/><br/>Not sure when I will have a chance, but there is a lot to say about this one. And it is one of those that I appreciated much more after Ive finished. </span>

